HEADWORD: Stirabout
<hw>Stir"a*bout`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A dish formed of
oatmeal boiled in water to a certain consistency and frequently stirred,
or of oatmeal and dripping mixed together and stirred about in a pan; a
hasty pudding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

